q3n (1.1.5-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add: wikipedia:// URI scheme (with optional language prefix)
  * Add: github:// URI scheme (owner/repo, issues, PRs, commits)
  * Add: Anki export plugin (app/plugins/anki/); q3n export -f anki
  * Fix: GUI dirty-flag bug — blockSignals during show_entry() field population
  * Fix: CLI cmd_export delegates to export_file() for all file-output formats
  * Fix: JS parser now supports osm://, geo:, overpass:// schemes
  * Fix: ConfigParser now uses interpolation=None (prevents % crash in config values)
  * Fix: bare except Exception narrowed to specific types in core/q3n.py
  * Fix: open_path in GUI now shows error dialog instead of silent pass
  * Fix: View menu added with plugin dock toggle action
  * Fix: setup.py uses find_packages() to include app/ and plugins
  * Fix: q3n config --install falls back to sys.prefix for examples path
  * Fix: debian/rules uses build/scripts-* glob (Python version-agnostic)
  * Chore: entry_dialog.py deleted (dead code); debian/install updated
  * Chore: CI now installs PySide6 and lints app/plugins/ and gui/
  * Chore: web/public/q3n-parser.js is now a symlink to src/js/q3n-parser.js
  * Docs: man page updated (all export formats, new schemes, fortune flags)
  * Bump version to 1.1.5

